{"name": "textmeld", "metadata": {"name": "textmeld", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "A tool to combine multiple text files into one for LLM training and prompts", "upload_time": 1735197613}, "documentation": ["# TextMeld\n\nA CLI tool that combines multiple text files into one, making it perfect for LLM training data preparation and prompt engineering.\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install textmeld\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```bash\n# Basic usage\ntextmeld /path/to/your/directory\n\n# Set maximum directory depth\ntextmeld /path/to/your/directory --max-depth 3\n```\n\nThe tool will:\n1. Respect .gitignore patterns if present\n2. Include README.md content if available\n3. Combine all text files into a single output\n4. Skip binary and hidden files automatically\n\n## Supported File Types\n\n- Markdown (.md)\n- Text (.txt)\n- YAML (.yaml, .yml)\n- JSON (.json)\n- Python (.py)\n- JavaScript (.js)\n- TypeScript (.ts)\n- JSX/TSX (.jsx, .tsx)\n- HTML (.html)\n- CSS (.css)\n\n## Contributing\n\nContributions are welcome! Please feel free to submit a Pull Request."], "modules": [{"name": "textmeld", "documentation": ["TextMeld - A tool to combine multiple text files into one for LLM training and prompts"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "textmeld.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "textmeld.main", "xref": {"fqname": "textmeld.core.main", "project": null}}, {"name": "textmeld.ProjectAnalyzer", "xref": {"fqname": "textmeld.core.ProjectAnalyzer", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "textmeld.constants", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "textmeld.constants.READABLE_EXTENSIONS", "type": {"name": "